title: The new Dyson DC58 product in use - Official Dyson Video
description:
To explore the technology behind the latest Dyson Digital Slim cordless vacuum cleaner

The new Dyson Digital Slim DC59 Animal is powered by the Dyson digital motor V6. Running at up to 110,000rpm, this works with our 2 Tier Radial cyclone technology and a re-engineered nickel manganese cobalt battery to provide powerful, constant suction. The latest motorised head with carbon fibre filaments aids in achieving high dust removal. Together these four technologies enable DC59 Animal to suck up as much dust as even a corded vacuum and delivers 3 times the suction of any other cordless vacuum cleaner.

transcripts: DC 58 is the latest dyson handheld machine with three times the suction power of any other hand held in use it's our most powerful yet. The dyson digital motor v6 sits at the heart of DC 58 spinning it up to 110 thousand rpm up to three times faster than conventional motors - two radial cyclones generate high centrifugal forces to increase airflow and capture fine dust DC 58 re-engineered battery provides 20 minutes of powerful fade-free suction or six minutes in boost mode for more difficult tasks.
